Joburg didn't disappoint with hundreds of people taking to the streets to celebrate Pride's 30th anniversary. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Joburg didn't disappoint, with hundreds of people taking to the streets to celebrate Pride's 30th anniversary. Parts of Sandton were shut down on Saturday in the name of creating awareness around challenges facing the LGBTQI community. WATCH: Johannesburg Pride celebrating 30th anniversary A  new flag representing all 54 African countries also made its debut. The festival pushes for the greater tolerance and inclusion of the LGBTQI community across the continent.